1.title: Failure Is Not an Option
1.plot: With an impossible deadline, Titan moves forward to manufacture parts for thermal night vision scopes. After committing to a job with IR Defense, Titan seeks to help equip America's special forces by rallying his team to overcome the enormous challenges.

2.title: Training Day
2.plot: Titan takes a break from the daily grind to help out a twelve year US Marine Veteran launch an elite American manufacturing facility. After fighting for our freedom, James Hampton and his cousin put everything on the line to see M1 Machining succeed.

3.title: Mission Critical
3.plot: TITAN goes to college when the students of USC's Rocket Team come calling. Attempting to make world history with an all student designed rocket, Team TITAN is asked to make last minute, mission critical parts. TITAN helps a local women's shelter.

4.title: Walk in Victory
4.plot: TITAN sets out to design and manufacture an all California Built Fitness Rig for Third Space Cross-fit. With the grand opening approaching fast, there's no room for error as Third Space reaches for the American Dream.

5.title: Tides of Technology (Part 1 of 2)
5.plot: Coming full circle, TITAN gets a call to produce solar parts for the school in Maui that rescued him off the streets as a teen. TITAN visits his old prison to start a mentorship program for inmates being released.

6.title: Tides of Technology (Part 2 of 2)
6.plot: Coming full circle, TITAN who was once homeless on Maui, is contacted by a local firm to manufacture parts for the Scorpio 5 Space Lab. TITAN works with students to bring technology to the island.

7.title: Going Big
7.plot: TITAN and his team go after the American Dream. HUGE opportunities lead to HUGE rewards with a new machine shop facility, an even bigger truck for TITAN, and the arrival of a 5-Axis machine from Haas Automation. It's TEAM TITAN at a whole new level!

8.title: Machining the Future of Transportation
8.plot: With aggressive machining and a new shop, TEAM TITAN partners with a visionary company to change the future of the transportation industry. TITAN also manages his son's decision to forego college and pursue a career in American Manufacturing.

9.title: Challenging Titanium
9.plot: Pushing the limits of Titanium to the extreme, TITAN machines a part to help sustain lives while deep sea diving. Oceanic, leaders within the deep sea diving industry, call on TEAM TITAN to bring their 20 year vision to life.

10.title: Last Metal Standing
10.plot: NASCAR driver Jason Patison gets more than he bargained for when TITAN redesigns a crucial component out of the indestructible material, Inconel. Also, key members of TEAM TITAN tackle new challenges.

11.title: The Art of Manufacturing
11.plot: Machines making machines. Automated robots building parts around the clock. America gets to see machining at a whole new level when TITAN visits Haas Automation as he draws back the curtain on the art of manufacturing.

12.title: Unveiling the Future
12.plot: Autodesk, a multi-billion dollar company, lays down a challenge for TITAN to build parts for their new state-of-the-art 3D printer. The future of American Manufacturing is revealed.

13.title: Call to Action
13.plot: The stakes are raised when TITAN meets with Scott Paul, President of the Alliance for American Manufacturing based in Washington D.C., to reinvision the foundations of our great country. The time for real change is NOW.

imdb.plot outline: "In the first season of TITAN American Built, Titan pulls back the curtains to reveal American manufacturing like its never been seen before. Each week, great American companies in different industries are featured and profiled. From aerospace, to deep sea, to motorsports, to our own military, Titan and his team of manufacturing experts show how we as Americans can still out-compete the rest of the world - all while showcasing advanced machining, technology and the greatest workforce on the planet, the American workforce. Each episode of TITAN will expose the compassionate, humanitarian side of Titan Gilroy. Titan has not forgotten where he has come from. Having overcome huge obstacles in his own life, Titan is passionate about helping others do the same. Watch as Titan uses his platform and journeys across our great nation, spreading his message of hope. A homeless women's shelter, his old prison, a youth correctional camp and an innovative high school all learn firsthand what it truly means to be American Built. American manufacturing was once a great symbol of our freedom. An industry that allowed us to control our own destiny, to produce our own goods, and employ our own people. It is time that we stand up and fight for that right once again. It is time that we fight for our jobs and fight for our workers. Join with us as we Fight for America."
